<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Entitlements for Messages for AI (hardened-runtime, non-sandboxed).

  JIT (v0.3.0):

  `com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit` and `com.apple.security.cs.allow-
  unsigned-executable-memory` are REQUIRED for any Bun-compiled inner
  Mach-O (imessage-drafts-mcp, whatsapp-drafts-mcp, whatsapp-drafts-
  daemon). Bun uses a JavaScript JIT and an FFI trampoline JIT —
  Hardened Runtime SIGTRAPs the process the first time it tries to
  map writable+executable pages without these entitlements. Symptom
  before the fix: WhatsApp daemon exited status=5 (SIGTRAP) ~2-3s
  after spawn, the moment the menubar's first RPC call invoked
  peer-auth's FFI-backed getsockopt/proc_pidpath path. imessage-drafts-
  mcp never crashed in the wild only because its short-lived stdio
  calls didn't hit the JIT-needed code paths often enough to trigger.

  Apple Events scope (v0.1.1, PR 5b code-review finding #10):

  `com.apple.security.automation.apple-events` is required for ANY
  Apple Event sending under hardened-runtime. Removing it would break
  the menubar's send path (DraftSender.swift calls Messages.app via
  AppleScript). The user's TCC consent prompt gates each new target
  app the first time it's contacted, so the actual scope at runtime
  is still bounded by user consent — but the *static* entitlement
  allows AE to any scriptable app.

  `com.apple.security.scripting-targets` below declares INTENT:
  Messages.app is the only target the app expects to send to. This
  entry is enforced for sandboxed apps but is documentation-only for
  the non-sandboxed hardened-runtime case we're in here. Properly
  enforcing the scope requires turning the menubar into a sandboxed
  app (com.apple.security.app-sandbox + temporary-exception entries
  for ~/.messages-mcp/ filesystem access) — that's a larger refactor
  deferred to v0.1.2.

  When that refactor lands: add `<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
  <true/>` and a `<key>com.apple.security.temporary-exception.files.
  home-relative-path.read-write</key><array><string>.messages-mcp/
  </string></array>` block so the sidecar + drafts writes still work.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.personal-information.addressbook</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.automation.apple-events</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.scripting-targets</key>
    <dict>
        <key>com.apple.iChat</key>
        <array/>
    </dict>
</dict>
</plist>
